  "text": "K. sacchari type strain SP1T is a Gram-negative, non-spore-forming, motile rod with peritrichous flagella (Figure 1 ., Table 1 . [CITATION_1] ). It grows aerobically but reduces N2 to NH3 at a low pO2. It is able to grow and fix N2 on media containing 10% (w/v) cane sugar or sucrose and forms circular, convex, smooth colonies with entire margins on solid media. It grows best around 30°C and pH 7. Phylogenetic analysis of the 16S rRNA gene sequences from SP1T, the type strains of species of the genus Enterobacter and the type strains of type species of other genera in the family Enterobacteriaceae showed that SP1T formed a monophyletic group with the type strain of E. cloacae (the type species of the genus Standards in Genomic Sciences Enterobacter) [CITATION_2] . However, phylogenetic analysis of the rpoB gene sequences showed that SP1T diverged from E. cloacae [CITATION_3] . Here ",
